Company History

🔹 2003

Founded by Fred Luddy as GlideSoft, Inc.
Focused on providing Application Service Provider (ASP) solutions and workflow automation.

🔹 2004–2005

Development of the ServiceNow platform began using cloud-based architecture.

🔹 2006

GlideSoft was officially renamed to ServiceNow.
The company shifted focus toward IT Service Management (ITSM) delivered as Software-as-a-Service (SaaS).

🔹 2012

ServiceNow became a publicly traded company on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE: NOW).

🔹 Today

ServiceNow is a leading digital workflow platform serving IT, HR, Customer Service, Security Operations, and more.
